page.title: 01ST.AGNES HEAD
page.content: THE AREA IS LARGELY SEA BUT INCLUDES A SMALL FRINGE OF THE NORTH CORNISH COAST.THE PROMINANT HEADLAND OF ST.AGNES HEAD JUTS OUT INTO THE ATLANTIC OCEAN AND AFFORDS AN EXCELLENT VANTAGE POINT FOR THE COASTGUARD LOOKOUT SITED THERE.{THE {COASTAL FOOTPATH}SKIRTS THE HEADLAND BUT TAKE CARE! THE CLIFFS ARE BOTH HIGH AND EXPOSED.THERE ARE SEVERAL DISUSED TIN MINES IN THE AREA, A RELIC OF ITS FORMER PROSPERITY AND A FEW OUTLYING FARMS WHOSE FIELDS ARE MOSTLY PASTURE. MUCH OF THE LAND HOWEVER IS ROUGH CLIFFTOP GRASSLAND AND PART OF THIS HAS BEEN SET ASIDE AS A{PICNIC AREA}TO TAKE ADVANTAGE OF THE MARVELLOUS SEA VIEWS.
